            <title>[CXF-5186] SOAP 1.2 fault reason xml:lang attribute not properly parsed on client side</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5186</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4790&quot; title=&quot;Set lang and subcode for soapfault&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-4790&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-4790&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed the subcode in the SOAP 1.2 faults. The patch for that included also a partial fix for having xml:lang attribute properly written on the message going on the wire (server response). The problem is that the xml:lang attribute is still not properly parsed on client side, so it&apos;s not possible to get the actual fault reason message locale using the saaj api on client side.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
